  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "When booking a flight with Royal Air Maroc, you can usually pre-select your seat through the following steps:\n\n1. **During Booking**: When you initially book your flight on Royal Air Maroc\u2019s website, after selecting your flight details, you\u2019ll be given an option to choose your seat. This is often part of the booking process before you finalize your ticket purchase.\n\n2. **Manage My Booking**: If you have already booked your flight and want to select or change your seat, you can do so by visiting the \u201cManage My Booking\u201d section on their website. You will need your booking reference number and last name to access your reservation.\n\n3. **Mobile App**: If you have the Royal Air Maroc mobile app, you can also select your seat through the app by accessing your booking.\n\n4. **Customer Service**: If you encounter any difficulties online, you can contact Royal Air Maroc\u2019s customer service for assistance in selecting or changing your seat.\n\n5. **Airport Check-In**: If you are unable to pre-select a seat online, you can also choose your seat during check-in at the airport. However, availability might be limited at this stage.\n\nNote that for certain seats, such as those with extra legroom, there may be an additional charge. Always check their policy or contact them directly if you have specific seating requests or questions.",
